SanDisk has unveiled its latest USB flash sticks. The first unit is a USB Type-C device that can hold 1TB of data and is the “world’s smallest 1TB USB device”, said the company. SanDisk also revealed the world’s smallest 256GB USB flash drive. The 256GB SanDisk Ultra Fit USB 3.1 stick features a low-profile design, and is also available in smaller capacities. The Ultra Fit flash drives feature read speeds of up to 130MB/s.